  <h3>3. Other adverbal uses of <em>mar</em></h3>
  <p><mark>mar sin</mark>
    <small class="text-muted">‘therefore’</small>, <mark>mar as àbhaist</mark>
    <small class="text-muted">‘as usual’</small>, <mark>mar as trice</mark>
    <small class="text-muted">‘usually’</small>, <mark>mar a thuirt i</mark>
    <small class="text-muted">‘as she said’</small>, etc. <small><a data-toggle="collapse" href="#other-adverbal">more/less</a></small></p>
  <div class="collapse" id="other-adverbal">
    <p>Both as a preposition and a conjunction, <strong>mar</strong> is used in a range of other, more idiomatic adverbal expressions.</p>
    <h5>
      <em>mar sin</em>
    </h5>
    <p>‘so’, ‘therefore’, ‘for that reason’</p>
